==English==

===Etymology===
English began using this term in 1789. The name probably came into English through Spanish.

===Proper noun===
'''Miskito''' (''plural:'' '''[[Miskitos]]''' ''or'' '''Miskito''')
# A member of the Amerindian people who dwell/dwelt on the Atlantic coastline of Nicaragua and Honduras.
# The [[w:Miskito language|Miskito language]].

